This paper discusses the performance of various Multi-Armed Bandit (MAB) strategies in the context of regret minimization, which is a common topic in the machine learning and artificial intelligence community (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also deals with non-stationary reward functions and delayed feedback, which are relevant topics in the field of control systems (cs.SY) and game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper involves simulations and data analysis, which are common in the field of data science (cs.DS).
